Since all the supergravity models under consideration fall within
the scope of the above theorem, it is now immediate to determine
the associated billiard Kac-Moody algebra. The results are
collected in table I of the concluding section. Note, as a further
check, that the highest root  is always non
degenerate for these models (see table VI in chapter X of
). This is necessary because we have seen that
 is a symmetry wall in higher dimensions, and
symmetry walls are never degenerate. A highest root
with multiplicity  is thus an obstruction to oxidation. Note
also that all the algebras  of the table are hyperbolic,
so that the models are all chaotic.

