but also the same Weyl group, W(A_1^ ) &&
W(A_2^(2)  ),

 W(C_2^ ) && W(A_4^(2)  )One of the interests of the billiard analysis is its connection
with -dualities and hidden symmetries of the theory,
for which various proposals exist
. We reserve for further
study a more detailed analysis of the significance of the twist in
the symmetry structure of the models where it appears.

Finally, we note that although derived with the purpose of
determining the billiard structure of supergravity theories,
our theorem makes no use of supersymmetry.  As stressed
previously, the only relevant datum
is the real symmetry group 
which characterizes the
manifold of the scalar fields coupled to gravity in the toroidal
compactification of the theory to three dimensions.


