A satisfactory feature of the class of overextensions
(standard and 
twisted) is that it is closed under duality.
For instance,  is dual to
.
In fact, one could get the twisted overextensions associated
with the highest short root from the standard overextensions
precisely by requiring closure
under duality.  A similar feature already holds
for the affine algebras.

